00:22:15.996 --> 00:22:17.636 A:middle
scrolling past to find other

00:22:17.636 --> 00:22:18.166 A:middle
content?

00:22:18.696 --> 00:22:20.296 A:middle
And, we use all this information

00:22:20.296 --> 00:22:22.326 A:middle
to understand what are the

00:22:22.326 --> 00:22:23.436 A:middle
different platters that the user

00:22:23.436 --> 00:22:24.736 A:middle
wants to see right on a wrist

00:22:24.736 --> 00:22:25.066 A:middle
raise.

00:22:26.016 --> 00:22:29.416 A:middle
And so, because we're trying to

00:22:29.416 --> 00:22:30.866 A:middle
surface, again, the content the

00:22:30.866 --> 00:22:32.726 A:middle
user cares about most, you want

00:22:32.726 --> 00:22:33.246 A:middle
to make sure that you're

00:22:33.246 --> 00:22:34.846 A:middle
providing relevant, engaging

00:22:34.846 --> 00:22:36.246 A:middle
content to be surfaced on the

00:22:36.246 --> 00:22:36.976 A:middle
Siri watch face.

00:22:40.796 --> 00:22:42.026 A:middle
So, let's talk a little bit more

00:22:42.026 --> 00:22:43.846 A:middle
about how we actually put your

00:22:43.846 --> 00:22:44.896 A:middle
relevant shortcuts on the Siri

00:22:44.896 --> 00:22:45.526 A:middle
watch face.

00:22:45.846 --> 00:22:47.346 A:middle
So, like Paul mentioned earlier,

00:22:47.406 --> 00:22:48.416 A:middle
the first step is you need to

00:22:48.416 --> 00:22:49.596 A:middle
provide your relevant shortcuts

00:22:49.596 --> 00:22:50.916 A:middle
to the system, into the

00:22:50.916 --> 00:22:52.806 A:middle
defaultRelevantShortcutsStore.

00:22:54.006 --> 00:22:54.986 A:middle
Once you've provided your

00:22:54.986 --> 00:22:56.946 A:middle
relevant shortcuts, we can run

00:22:56.946 --> 00:22:57.816 A:middle
them through our machine

00:22:57.816 --> 00:22:58.846 A:middle
learning model to figure out

00:22:58.926 --> 00:23:00.136 A:middle
what is the best way to be

00:22:58.926 --> 00:23:00.136 A:middle
what is the best way to be

00:23:00.136 --> 00:23:01.556 A:middle
surfacing your relevant

00:23:01.556 --> 00:23:02.466 A:middle
shortcuts to the user.

00:23:03.076 --> 00:23:04.236 A:middle
So, let's look at what we take

00:23:04.236 --> 00:23:05.336 A:middle
into account inside of this

00:23:05.486 --> 00:23:05.866 A:middle
model.

00:23:07.126 --> 00:23:08.546 A:middle
So, the first thing that we look

00:23:08.546 --> 00:23:10.116 A:middle
at is your relevance providers.

00:23:10.776 --> 00:23:12.496 A:middle
This is your way to provide

00:23:12.496 --> 00:23:14.356 A:middle
additional context to the system

00:23:14.626 --> 00:23:15.786 A:middle
that we wouldn't otherwise have.

00:23:16.066 --> 00:23:17.506 A:middle
This might be a concrete time,

00:23:17.766 --> 00:23:19.696 A:middle
location, or other context.

00:23:21.286 --> 00:23:22.756 A:middle
We also look at past behavior.

00:23:22.826 --> 00:23:24.416 A:middle
So, how has the user interacted

00:23:24.416 --> 00:23:25.506 A:middle
with this relevant shortcut

00:23:25.536 --> 00:23:25.936 A:middle
before?

00:23:26.356 --> 00:23:27.176 A:middle
Is it something they're spending

00:23:27.176 --> 00:23:28.496 A:middle
a lot of time tapping on and

00:23:28.496 --> 00:23:29.626 A:middle
looking at on the watch face?

00:23:29.936 --> 00:23:30.436 A:middle
Or, something that they're

00:23:30.436 --> 00:23:31.956 A:middle
scrolling past to find something

00:23:32.046 --> 00:23:32.666 A:middle
more interesting?

00:23:34.506 --> 00:23:36.076 A:middle
We also look at a number of

00:23:36.076 --> 00:23:37.166 A:middle
different factors from across

00:23:37.196 --> 00:23:38.536 A:middle
the system, such as, you know,

00:23:38.536 --> 00:23:39.916 A:middle
the current time, current day of

00:23:39.916 --> 00:23:41.666 A:middle
the week, current location,

00:23:41.666 --> 00:23:43.646 A:middle
user's routine, among a number

00:23:43.646 --> 00:23:44.456 A:middle
of other factors.

00:23:44.516 --> 00:23:46.126 A:middle
And, take all this into account

00:23:46.366 --> 00:23:48.146 A:middle
to try to better understand what

00:23:48.146 --> 00:23:49.746 A:middle
is the context under which the

00:23:49.746 --> 00:23:51.096 A:middle
user wants to interact with the

00:23:51.096 --> 00:23:52.116 A:middle
particular shortcut.

00:23:52.626 --> 00:23:57.296 A:middle
And, it's also worth noting that

00:23:57.296 --> 00:23:59.406 A:middle
this model is secure and

00:23:59.406 --> 00:24:00.676 A:middle
personalized to each user.

00:23:59.406 --> 00:24:00.676 A:middle
personalized to each user.

00:24:01.066 --> 00:24:02.526 A:middle
All of our learning happens

00:24:02.636 --> 00:24:05.496 A:middle
on-device, and we're building a

00:24:05.496 --> 00:24:07.306 A:middle
model for each and every single

00:24:07.306 --> 00:24:08.806 A:middle
user of the Siri watch face.

00:24:08.876 --> 00:24:10.126 A:middle
The way that you interact with

00:24:10.126 --> 00:24:11.226 A:middle
the watch face may be different

00:24:11.226 --> 00:24:12.116 A:middle
from the way that I interact

00:24:12.116 --> 00:24:12.646 A:middle
with the watch.

00:24:14.146 --> 00:24:15.546 A:middle
And, once we have this model

00:24:15.546 --> 00:24:17.436 A:middle
trained we can then take your

00:24:17.436 --> 00:24:19.326 A:middle
relevant shortcuts, and again,

00:24:19.406 --> 00:24:20.586 A:middle
surface them on the Siri watch

00:24:20.586 --> 00:24:21.796 A:middle
face based on their relevance to

00:24:21.796 --> 00:24:21.976 A:middle
the user.

00:24:26.416 --> 00:24:27.376 A:middle
If you attended some of the

00:24:27.376 --> 00:24:29.136 A:middle
previous shortcut talks, you may

00:24:29.136 --> 00:24:30.396 A:middle
have heard about donations.

00:24:31.126 --> 00:24:32.726 A:middle
This is your way to indicate to

00:24:32.726 --> 00:24:34.606 A:middle
the system what the user's doing

00:24:34.606 --> 00:24:35.266 A:middle
within your app.

00:24:36.846 --> 00:24:37.926 A:middle
And, although they don't

00:24:37.926 --> 00:24:39.186 A:middle
actually surface within the UI

00:24:39.186 --> 00:24:41.816 A:middle
of the Siri watch face, we take

00:24:41.816 --> 00:24:43.176 A:middle
them into account when trying to

00:24:43.176 --> 00:24:44.346 A:middle
understand the user's past

00:24:44.346 --> 00:24:44.886 A:middle
behavior.

00:24:47.416 --> 00:24:49.556 A:middle
So, again, donations are your

00:24:49.556 --> 00:24:51.406 A:middle
way to indicate important tasks,

00:24:51.746 --> 00:24:53.186 A:middle
or other information about what

00:24:53.186 --> 00:24:54.816 A:middle
users are doing inside of your

00:24:54.816 --> 00:24:56.416 A:middle
applications, and providing that

00:24:56.416 --> 00:24:56.936 A:middle
to the system.

00:24:58.546 --> 00:25:00.006 A:middle
And, by giving this information

00:24:58.546 --> 00:25:00.006 A:middle
And, by giving this information

00:25:00.006 --> 00:25:01.996 A:middle
to the system, we can understand

00:25:01.996 --> 00:25:03.276 A:middle
and learn patterns in the user's

00:25:03.276 --> 00:25:03.836 A:middle
behavior.

00:25:03.836 --> 00:25:06.646 A:middle
So, if the user, for example, is

00:25:06.646 --> 00:25:07.766 A:middle
looking or performing the same

00:25:07.766 --> 00:25:08.996 A:middle
action at the same time every

00:25:08.996 --> 00:25:10.966 A:middle
single day, or around similar

00:25:10.966 --> 00:25:12.746 A:middle
locations, the system can pick

00:25:12.746 --> 00:25:14.186 A:middle
up on these patterns, and again,

00:25:14.186 --> 00:25:15.526 A:middle
surface the relevant shortcuts

00:25:15.556 --> 00:25:16.956 A:middle
when they're appropriate to your

00:25:16.956 --> 00:25:17.456 A:middle
users.

00:25:19.236 --> 00:25:21.886 A:middle
So, if you're using

00:25:21.886 --> 00:25:23.426 A:middle
NSUserActivities to represent

00:25:23.566 --> 00:25:25.286 A:middle
your donations, there's a few

00:25:25.286 --> 00:25:26.416 A:middle
things you need to do to be able

00:25:26.536 --> 00:25:27.576 A:middle
to provide those donations to

00:25:27.576 --> 00:25:28.066 A:middle
the system.

00:25:28.706 --> 00:25:30.056 A:middle
The first is you need to set

00:25:30.106 --> 00:25:31.296 A:middle
both these properties to "true"

00:25:31.296 --> 00:25:32.856 A:middle
in your NSUserActivity, the

00:25:32.856 --> 00:25:34.096 A:middle
eligibleForPrediction and

00:25:34.096 --> 00:25:35.066 A:middle
eligibleForSearch.

00:25:37.056 --> 00:25:38.156 A:middle
Next, you need to make sure that

00:25:38.156 --> 00:25:39.436 A:middle
your user activity is supported

00:25:39.436 --> 00:25:40.936 A:middle
by an application, by indicating

00:25:40.936 --> 00:25:42.206 A:middle
that within your info.plist.

00:25:43.936 --> 00:25:44.926 A:middle
And, finally you want to make

00:25:44.926 --> 00:25:46.056 A:middle
sure that you're donating these

00:25:46.056 --> 00:25:47.196 A:middle
